Phishing;
- Mix of Social Engineering and Poofing
- Re-creating famous website to steal information to the users
- Stealing information by collecting credentials  that the user inputted in the phishing website
- Impersonating higher level of people or company
--------------------------------------
Vishing;
- Fake security checks or bank updates
- Most commonly in phone
--------------------------------------
Spear Phishing;
- Specifically narrowing people down of a community (mostly in company, organizations, etc.)
--------------------------------------
Whaling;
- Targeting people that are in high level and aiming to gather their credentials through it.

March 19 2016 - The Big Phish - Whaling attack
---------------------------------------
Tailgating;
- Using someone else to gain access to a building

Prevention on Tailgating;
- Policy for Visitors
- One scan, one person
- Mantrap / Airlock
- Don't be afraid to ask questions?
----------------------------------------
Impersonation;
- Pretend to be someone you aren't 
- Collecting information in the dumpster and well throughout research
- Attack someone and asking for a specifically senstive using higher level person name
- Being a Buddy
- Throw tons of technical information

Preventing on Impersonation;
- Never volunteer infromation
- Don't disclose personal details
- Always verify before revealing info
- Verification should be encourage
----------------------------------------
Dumpster Diving;
- Looking for important information that might be dangerous for people
- Making use of important information to impersonate someones name, or phone numbers
- Timing information to gather information in the dumpster
-----------------------------------------
Shoulder Surfing;
- Looking in the screen of the worker and trying to get a glimpse of company information through it.
(Airports, Hallway-facing Monitors, Coffee Shops)

Surf from afar;
- Binoculars / Telescope
- Webcam Monitoring

Preventing Shoulder Surfing;
- Control your input in the Screen
- Use Privacy Filter
- Keep your monitor out of sight (Away from windows and hallways)
- Be careful on the people around you
-------------------------------------------
Computer Hoaxes;
- A threat the doesn't actually exist, but they seem like they could be real
- Consumed a lots of resources
- Hoaxes that will take your money
- Often an Email, Websites, etc.
- A hoax about a virus can waste much time

Prevent Hoaxing;
- Believe no one in the internet
- Cross reference;
-- hoax-slayer.net
-- snopes.com
- Use Spam filters
- If its sounds too good to be true
--------------------------------------------
Watering Hole Attack;
- Threat actor doing a research and infecting network location on where your team is going 
- Infecting the third part sites through site vulnerability and email attachments
- Infect all visitors 

Defense on attack;
- Good Firewall and IDS
- Add Layered defense in your computer
- Anti-virus / Anti-malware signature updates
---------------------------------------------
Social Engineeering Attack;
- Doesn't involve any device but in person attack on gathering information
- May involve multiple people that target one person in organization
- Phone calls
- Emailed Funeral Notifications

Principles of Social Engineering;
Authority
-- In charge of the company or have a specific role
Intimidation
-- Bad things that will happen if you don't help them
Consensus / Social proof
-- Convince based on what's normally expected
Scarcity
-- Situation will only happen in a certain amount of time
Urgency
-- Works alongside scarcity, Act quickly and don't think
Familiarity
-- Someone you know, or is being close as friend to you
Trust
- Someone who will feel safe or trying to help you
---------------------------------------------
Denial of Service;
- Force a service to fail by taking advantage of design failure or vulnerability
- Create a smokescreen for some other exploits
- Cause a system to be unavailable (competitive exploitation)

Friendly DoS
- Unintentional DoSing 
- Network DoS (Layer 2 loop without STP)
- Bandwidth DoS (Downloading multi-gigabyte linux distro over a DSL line)

DDoS - Launch an army of computers to bring down a service
-- traffic spike
-- using of botnets
-- Asymmetric threat (fewer resources than the victim)

DDoS Amplification;
- Turn your small attack into a big attack
- Turning internet services against the victim
- Protocol Abuses
-----------------------------------------------






